Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_visible_netGroups(25.10)                      set_visible_netGroups(25.10)

Name
       set_visible_netGroups - Displays only the specified netGroups and hides
       all other netGroups

Syntax
       set_visible_netGroups

       [-help]

       {<netGroups> | -all}

       Displays only the specified netGroups and hides all other netGroups.

       To display all netGroups, specify the -all parameter.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each set_visible_netGroups parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man set_visible_netGroups

       -all   Displays all the netGroups.

       <netGroups>
              Displays  only  the specified netGroups and hides all other net-
              Groups. You can specify multiple netGroup names.

Examples
              * The following command hides all netGroups except the specified
                one:

                set_visible_netGroups test_ng

Related Information
              * get_visible_netGroups

